   <info>
      <title>Migrate from SMT to RMT</title>
   </info>
   <para>This chapter describes the migration from SMT on SLES 11 or 12 to RMT on SLES 15.</para>
   <sect1 xml:id="sec-rmt-migrate-notes">
      <title>Important notes</title>
      <warning>
         <title>Read this section carefully</title>
         <para>Carefully read this section. It contains vital information about the migration process.</para>
      </warning>
      <variablelist>
         <varlistentry>
            <term>Use a new host</term>
            <listitem>
               <para>We recommend that you install RMT on a newly installed SLES 15 host. RMT is not a complete replacement for SMT. It has a different workflow than SMT and only supports registering SUSE Linux Enterprise Server 12 systems and newer.</para>
            </listitem>
         </varlistentry>
         <varlistentry>
            <term>Repository metadata and settings</term>
            <listitem>
               <para>The settings of staged repositories are <emphasis>not</emphasis> exported from SMT. Repositories that have been marked to be mirrored are exported.</para>
            </listitem>
         </varlistentry>
         <varlistentry>
            <term>Custom repositories</term>
            <listitem>
               <para>It is only possible to export repositories that are marked for mirroring.</para>
            </listitem>
         </varlistentry>
         <varlistentry>
            <term>Expired subscriptions</term>
            <listitem>
               <para>Products no longer available on the organization subscriptions will not be available on RMT.</para>
            </listitem>
         </varlistentry>
         <varlistentry>
            <term>Client information</term>
            <listitem>
               <para>Systems and their activated products are exported. SMT client jobs and patch status are not exported from SMT.</para>
            </listitem>
         </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
